        "type": "university",
        "description": "The Ceibal project is a Uruguayan initiative to implement the \"One Laptop per Child\" model to introduce Information and Communication Technologies (ICT) in primary education and secondary schools.\nIn four years, Ceibal delivered 450,000 laptops to all students and teachers in the primary education system and no-cost internet access throughout the country. As of 2009, results included increased self-esteem in students, improved motivation of students and teachers, and active participation by parents (94% approved of the plan, according to a national survey performed in 2009)."
    },
